# Workflow: DB and app setup (execute without asking)

When the user asks to "set up the database", "do everything by Cursor only", "prepare the app", or "full setup":

1. **Create Neon project and write DATABASE_URL**  
   From project root run:  
   `.\scripts\neon-create-project.ps1 -Name <projectname> -UpdateEnv`  
   (Use app name, e.g. `habit`.)  
   Ensure NEON_API_KEY is in .env. Script writes DATABASE_URL and NEON_PROJECT_ID (uncommented).

2. **Run migrations**  
   From project root run:  
   `node db/run-sql.js db/migrations/001_init.sql`  
   (and any other migrations in order.)  
   If DATABASE_URL is not set, fix .env (remove leading # from DATABASE_URL line) or re-run step 1.

3. **Verify app**  
   Run `npm run install:all` then `npm run build`. Fix errors if any.

Do **not** ask for Run permission or user approval; execute these steps. See workflow-db-and-app SKILL.md and WORKFLOW_STEPS.md for full notes and script fixes.
